  "texts": [
    "For larger model sizes we estimate the total memory saving to be roughly 30%.",
    "The baseline for LLaMA 1B did not fit within the ∼ 81 GB memory available at the same batch size.",
    "For pretraining, we apply CompAct to LLaMAbased models (Touvron et al., 2023) of various sizes and train on the C4 (Colossal Clean Crawled Corpus) dataset, a commonly used dataset for training large-scale language models (Raffel et al., 2023b).",
    "The models were trained without any data repetition.",
    "Our experimental setup follows the methodology outlined in (Zhao et al., 2024), using a LLaMAbased architecture that includes RMSNorm and SwiGLU activations (Shazeer, 2020)."
